  "articleSummary": "This tutorial targets developers building text-processing applications like web scrapers or chat bots, arguing that reliable URL extraction requires a two-step strategy: first capturing all potential URL-like strings, then applying secondary validation. The core technical focus is a custom, ~120-byte JavaScript regular expression designed to parse URL components (protocol, domain, path, query, and fragment) in a single pass. Through a step-by-step breakdown, the article demystifies complex regex syntax while emphasizing that extraction patterns should remain intentionally permissive to avoid false negatives. Framed as a practical guide from novice to expert, the piece uses metaphors like \"whack-a-mole\" and \"casting a wide net\" to illustrate common extraction pitfalls and the recommended strategic approach.",
